      <trans-unit id="11256" identifier="4f873e05c374cf0c90a2c80a5341b904">
        <source>The last parity bit placed is useful because it will always work for both the
column and row; if it doesn't match for both the row and column then you'll
have made a mistake with one of the cards, and should go back and check them
(try to not make it obvious that you're doing that).</source>
        <target>crwdns11256:0crwdne11256:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /p[30]</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11257" identifier="094e647401a9db0aaffc5f83225fb11a">
